	�ѦҤ��m�ޥΤ��d�ҡG(�`�N�G�W�L��ӥH�W�h�Hdash�s��)

	State space averaging techniques are commonly used in the analysis and control design of pulse width modulated (PWM) 
	power electronic systems [1]-[3]. However, it was not until recently that regious mathematical justification [3], [4] was given
	that theoretically explained the applications of these averaging techniques. As [3] and [5] have pointed out, the theoretical 
	development of PWM systems lags far behind many practical control applications.

